<sec id="id-2e4996d9-18de-4574-a30d-06c51521b572"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="14c34deb-4dc7-4c6c-e291-4016f0a3b5dd" timestamp="1656533506044"?>Related actions and expectations<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="14c34deb-4dc7-4c6c-e291-4016f0a3b5dd"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="64c0fd6a-d27b-4f5d-d04f-611de7922dc2" timestamp="1656533500971"?>The organization should:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="64c0fd6a-d27b-4f5d-d04f-611de7922dc2"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="ffe6528f-0df2-4a5e-f5b3-937257c2a13f" timestamp="1656533500971"?><list-item id="id-00a7bd9b-0f3d-4e5e-ee7b-6c7f0060af8c"><p>avoid preconceptions and prejudice in all <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ffe6528f-0df2-4a5e-f5b3-937257c2a13f"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="51cb3361-cdfc-4049-d621-3defd58515e4" text="its " timestamp="1666800238017"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="4aa7525a-f444-40c9-fad5-10d21ba9e872" timestamp="1656533500971"?>purchasing decisions. All suppliers, including local organizations and small and medium-sized organizations, should benefit from fair trading conditions;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-d07fa799-bf4d-4388-be4f-813e747d0feb"><p>respect, consider and defend the interests of stakeholders that are affected by its procurement activities;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-cc9a5d00-d6fc-4259-81f6-1eab537c70a0"><p>apply purchasing criteria pertaining to gender equality;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-cc5bd8fc-409a-4810-c171-d95c0bf90da7"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4aa7525a-f444-40c9-fad5-10d21ba9e872"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="c3d212d4-d092-4047-9d2f-85da8a212666" timestamp="1668787882168"?>ask suppliers to share their <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c3d212d4-d092-4047-9d2f-85da8a212666"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="e6755a3f-09aa-42da-b15c-bc947485f231" text="their " timestamp="1670340319366"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="cbeafed6-2530-4b52-86df-0bd8467e92c6" timestamp="1668787882168"?>gender equality policies and support those suppliers who don't have such policies<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="cbeafed6-2530-4b52-86df-0bd8467e92c6"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="9a9e50bd-418b-4142-82ba-89b785482fdb" text=" yet" timestamp="1670340329141"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="491a861a-ffe5-4730-9404-3547735d6e12" timestamp="1668787882168"?>. The objective is not to change but to challenge the supplier by the client to evolve, which can be the main motivation for suppliers. <italic>[See <xref as:rid="#id-f575c105-640a-492a-8942-98f6345de152" ref-type="bibr" id="id-f73f8211-255f-406d-876e-93ba503fb23a" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref> ISO 26000:2010, Guidance on social responsibility, clause 2.19 sphere of influence; and <xref as:rid="#id-d44f2acc-0bd8-4f81-bbb6-807a686c71e5" ref-type="bibr" id="id-ad3b30ed-7cab-4833-b4a2-ff564a22822c" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>ISO 30415:2021, Human resource management — Diversity and inclusion, section 11 External stakeholder relationship]</italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="491a861a-ffe5-4730-9404-3547735d6e12"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="9aecb4f8-84ba-4d1e-99f2-aa3481cd62e1" timestamp="1656533500971"?></p></list-item><list-item id="id-11b38020-90b8-4da2-b6b1-9ec67bf0308d"><p>invest in goods and <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9aecb4f8-84ba-4d1e-99f2-aa3481cd62e1"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="49809cba-3ced-4574-9a71-30a9254f4010" text="product" timestamp="1666856401179"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="c5cd5395-1c48-456b-ea06-54b0d22f0475" timestamp="1666856401179"?>service<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c5cd5395-1c48-456b-ea06-54b0d22f0475"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="541dd6c3-612c-40fa-d55a-5735db2167a6" timestamp="1656533500971"?>s that meet the needs of all the stakeholders, without any discrimination;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-2f689c3f-73d2-4128-d685-0edc86f40b28"><p>raise the awareness of<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="541dd6c3-612c-40fa-d55a-5735db2167a6"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="205cf536-b6b3-42e9-987f-2fbd5304db87" text=" its" timestamp="1666800398971"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="e8c80632-276a-463c-b5b8-2204db49f467" timestamp="1656533500971"?> suppliers on the question of <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e8c80632-276a-463c-b5b8-2204db49f467"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="01caad46-3681-44ab-aa22-b9e883bdcd44" timestamp="1666856444015"?>gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="01caad46-3681-44ab-aa22-b9e883bdcd44"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5855c1d8-9445-457f-d600-a6b377250dea" timestamp="1656533500971"?>equality by including clauses in its contracts that may be applied as criteria used to assess bids (condition of execution);</p></list-item><list-item id="id-95c8af73-2bdb-411c-ccc0-0b3012e126b1"><p>promote training and interaction with the organization's supply chain on the benefits of adopting gender equality practices.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5855c1d8-9445-457f-d600-a6b377250dea"?></p></list-item></list><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="bca9f3e5-795e-44a8-ceca-cd4a49320810" text="virtuous " timestamp="1666800369042"?></sec>